cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with human pose estimation from monocular image sequences, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel machine learning approach to solve the problem, which involves learning image-dependent structural constraints and sequence-dependent temporal context. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves predicting 3D poses, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
